      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 786: 🔴 Critical Issues - `injectEditionOverwrites()` documents that an empty `bodyOverwrite` clears the overwrite, but it actually stores `pluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d \"\"` on both the edited commit and, when latest, the original message. That leaves stale `bodyOverwrite` keys in the cached original and can make clients interpret an empty override differently from no override; it also conflicts with `clearBodyOverwrites()`, which erases the key. Make empty input erase the key consistently. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nif (bo.empty()) {\n    it-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData.erase(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n} else {\n    it-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d bo;\n}\n```\nApply the same erase-vs-set behavior when propagating to `originalIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData`.",
      "revId": "8a56050bc0272dbc44cb6e879f917321b5d03bce",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
