      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 1999: 🔴 Critical Issues - `loadMissingBodyOverwrites()` only writes back messages where the plugin returns a `bodyOverwrite` key. If a plugin decides a message needs no overwrite and leaves the key absent, that message remains permanently “missing” and will be sent through every future reload/load path, causing repeated plugin work and potentially repeated asynchronous transformations. Mark no-overwrite messages as processed with an empty value, matching the API documentation. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nconst auto boIt \u003d transformed.pluginData.find(\"bodyOverwrite\");\nif (boIt \u003d\u003d transformed.pluginData.end() || boIt-\u003esecond.empty()) {\n    if (const auto it \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(transformed.id);\n        it !\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end()) {\n        it-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d \"\";\n    }\n    continue;\n}\n```",
      "revId": "8a56050bc0272dbc44cb6e879f917321b5d03bce",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
